# Project Standards

## Product definition

- Origami is a **Go library** (`github.com/dpopsuev/origami`) providing graph-based agentic circuit orchestration.
- Purpose: enable domain-specific tools to define, walk, and observe circuits via a YAML DSL, typed Node/Edge/Graph interfaces, and AI-powered Extractors.
- Core primitives: Node, Edge, Graph, Walker, Extractor, Element, Persona, Mask, Adversarial Dialectic, Ouroboros (metacalibration).
- Design philosophy: low floor, high ceiling, wide walls (Papert Paradigm).

## Development methodology

- Start every story with Gherkin acceptance criteria (Given / When / Then).
- Follow the **Red-Orange-Green-Yellow-Blue** cycle (see `rules/universal/testing-methodology.mdc`).
- Run `go build ./...` and `go test ./...` after every change.
- Prefer deterministic outputs for identical inputs; seed ordering where needed.
- Zero domain imports: Origami must never import from consumer tools (Asterisk, Achilles, etc.).

## API stability

> **Applies only while PoC is the current goal.** When the "PoC Done" flag is raised (see `goals/`), flip this section to require deprecation-then-removal with a migration window. See `goals/poc-done-flips.md` for the full checklist.

- **Breaking changes are allowed.** Origami has exactly one consumer (Asterisk), owned and maintained by the same developer. There is no external API contract to preserve.
- **Delete over deprecate.** Do not leave `// Deprecated:` markers or backward-compat wrappers. Remove the old API and update the sole consumer in the same commit or session.
- **No shim layers.** If a type, function, or package is superseded, delete the original. Do not maintain parallel paths.

## Scope

- Framework-only code. Domain-specific logic belongs in consumer repositories.
- The framework provides batteries-included extractors for common formats (JSON, YAML, structured text) but domain-specific extractors are built by consumers.

## Reference implementations

| Tool | Repository | Domain |
|------|-----------|--------|
| Asterisk | `github.com/dpopsuev/asterisk` (private) | Test CI root-cause analysis |
| Achilles | `github.com/dpopsuev/achilles` | AI-driven vulnerability discovery via meta-pattern recognition (initial targets: RHEL, OCP) |

## Data handling

- Treat external data as partial and potentially absent. Return partial results with clear errors.
- Redact secrets and PII in all outputs by default.
- All external calls require timeouts and retry with exponential backoff.
